title: Witchtown
description: When sixteen-year-old Macie O’Sullivan and her masterfully manipulative mother Aubra arrive at the gates of Witchtown—the most famous and mysterious witch-only haven in the world—they have one goal in mind: to rob it for all it’s worth.But that plan derails when Macie and Aubra start to dig deeper into Witchtown’s history and uncover that there is more to the quirky haven than meets the eye.Exploring the haven by herself, Macie finds that secrets are worth more than money in Witchtown.Secrets have their own power.
author: Cory Putman Oakes
